  <mads:note type="source">Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 1, 1867, p. 297: "Aristias, a dramatic poet, 
    the son of Pratinas, whose tomb Pausanias saw at Phlius..., and whose Satyric dramas, with those of his father, were
    surpassed only by those of Aeschylus...."</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Aristias, 2, of Phlius, tragedian, Tragic poet, son of Pratinas,
    with whose plays he came second after Aeschylus in 467 BC (DID C 4)...he came first in c. 460 BC (DID A 3a, 17)...." 
    Neudecker, Richard (Rom) Pressler, Frank (Heidelberg). "Aristias." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes
    edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2008. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 27 August 2008</mads:note>
